fields.name: Database
fields.basic: This is where all of your custom data and content goes, a place where you  can check any order you've ever had. Or any comment on a blog you've  ever had it is read only aswell so you never have to worry about any data going missing.
fields.extended: This is a read only database and cannot be queried using sql language and also  cannot be exported. You can however  query the database by adding filters or searching for key words or IDs

fields.name: Active Directory
fields.basic: This is where you will find every active user on your site and admin accounts it allows you to specify a role for  individuals helpful for when a team member joins your business and you  want them to help keep the website up to date!
fields.extended: Roles are non customisable. Admin will  be your role creator will be our role. and customers will have a member role by default any other roles you want to  specify please get in contact and we can set up a custom role for you.

fields.name: Financial page
fields.basic: This is where you will see things like total items sold. Total profit for this year. Total transaction value. Most cost  effective product. least sold, most sold most profitable etc. Your financial page depends very much on your business model. A blog for example will have very different options.
fields.extended: This will help with the tax return but it's not going to sort taxes out for you. It will  however potentially contain everything  you need other than expenses. Which if you want expenses recorded then that's something we can arrange.

fields.name: Calendar
fields.basic: If your products are bespoke when  someone orders a product it will let them know the expected delivery date  automatically based on the time it takes to make each product taking into  account how many hours you've  committed to creating products and how many other items are currently in the pipeline to be created. This may not be relevant for some sites.
fields.extended: Calendar is currently custom made and  doesn't have any export functionality or an API to update the calendar from  outside the website.

fields.name: Feature Wishlist
fields.basic: This is where you will submit and track your wishlist items you can change  priority remove and add items to your  wishlist at any point. You will see any  progress made and a price to unlock the change once it has completed. Not all wishlist items will go into development sometimes we will get in contact and  let you know of different ways to achieve the objective or let you know something isn't currently possible and offer an alternative.
fields.extended: These items are priority 3 under bugfixes and change requests.

fields.name: Edit/ add webpages
fields.basic: This is where you can add or edit new webpages it depending on your business needs there will be numerous templates  just for you to edit and even a fully functional website designer where you can freely edit your site. please check out our web designer and feel free to create and save templates so when you decide  to have your site built we can make them available to you.
fields.extended: You will be able to write custom HTML, JavaScript and CSS in the real version but for the sake of security we don't allow  custom java on the preview version.

fields.name: Themes
fields.basic: This is where you choose a theme for your admin page it changes the colour of your admin site and doesn't change  any of your live websites.
fields.extended: You can choose from premade selection of themes we are working on allowing  website owners to create their own  themes and name them. With the  intention of allowing them to be used by all other website owners in the future.

fields.name: Categories
fields.basic: This is where you can see the current categories on your website. This may or may not be relevant for your site but where it is applicable this will be where you can edit the available categories and  add options for the customers to choose from.
fields.extended: The categories will be set up ready for you and if you supply us with a list of  products, their price, and other relevant fields (preferably in an excel or google  sheet format) we will add the products to your site as well. Each product getting  it's own unique page of course.

fields.name: Admin site security
fields.basic: This site will only be accessible to you the website owner and anyone else with the admin role. The admin role cannot be assigned by anyone other than you. You will also be required to enter a code that only you have access to whenever  you enter your admin page allowing you access for 30 mins. After 30 mins you will have to enter the code again.
fields.extended: Every admin page will have it's own  background security checks and the  entire admin infrastructure will be on a  separate part of your site. Only accessible via your special link.

fields.name: Active Directory
fields.basic: Every user on your site is assigned a role in the active directory which changes what the can see and do. This means that someone who has got the role customer will never be able to do or change  anything to do with the site.
fields.extended: Roles are extremely complex bits of code every role is defined server side and we  will never make public any of the code. This means that no one will ever be able to change their role themselves other than through the Admin site which no one will even know exists as it won't be part of your domain.

fields.name: Secure Database
fields.basic: Although you will be able to see the data through your website. You will never be  able to interact with it. This means no one else can either. There are also some  very clever attack detecting bits of code  built into every form on your site which will protect you from any common form attacks as well.
fields.extended: Common attacks include SQL injection, DDOS, weak authentication and insecure system architecture.

fields.name: Firewall
fields.basic: Your admin site and database will sit  behind a basic firewall you can also pay  extra to improve the firewall if the data  you are storing is particularly dangerous.  This can also be something we can  discuss at anytime.
fields.extended: Basic firewall protects against direct  attempts to access the admin site. The more advanced firewall is either  Microsoft defender for the cloud or  sentinel or both. You can read more  about these here:

fields.name: GDPR
fields.basic: You might not be aware of this but all companies when interacting with customers digitally are supposed to have a record of processing. This in short is a description of what  happens to the customers data once they have signed up.
fields.extended: This is only needed when there is a  breach most of the time but sometimes it can be part of an audit done by the ICO so it's always best to have one.

fields.name: GDPR: subject access requests
fields.basic: Any user on your site can request all the  info you hold for them via a subject  access request while rare failure to comply  can result in nasty fines. We make it easy  to comply with this with our SAR creator. This will output text for you to copy and  paste to send to the requestor.
fields.extended: You have 1 month to respond to these. Please be aware it doesn't only include information you have stored on your site any paper documents or data elsewhere  about them they must also be shared  with the requestor. The SAR creator also guides you through the process.

fields.name: GDPR: The right to be forgotten
fields.basic: Any customer at any given moment can request permanent deletion of their personal information. Which you think would be very simple! But it's not sadly. We make deleting a user simple and also  make sure than no orders relating to the  customer are deleted instead they are anonymous from that point on instead.
fields.extended: Although rare you have 1 month to  comply. The system handles the delete action make sure you also destroy any  paper records regarding the customer.

fields.name: Templates
fields.basic: You can create your own or request  templates to be created for you in order for you to add new content to your  website whenever you want.
fields.extended: There's a simple designer available to all website creators where you can make your own templates but with all designers there are certain limitations so to help overcome that we offer to create custom templates with no limitations for you. Or you can use our advanced designer to  create your own you will need to at least know HTML and CSS languages.

fields.name: Wishlist
fields.basic: A wishlist is where you put your future ideas for your site. You don't need to do  anything else. If we get some free time in the office we will start to work on your wishlist items and make them a reality  once we have completed the item we will allow it to be unlockable. We may ask you for more details about your wishlist items to understand them better and update the description to match.
fields.extended: Wishlist items are not prioritised so they could be sat dormant for a very long time before being actioned or even looked at.

fields.name: Change requests
fields.basic: Sometimes when things are particularly important for you to get done you can upgrade a wish list item to a change request. A change request is you actively asking for some improvement or change to your site to be looked at immediately.
fields.extended: These changes are chargeable and we will work together to create a plan and make the change a reality.

fields.name: Flexible delivery
fields.basic: Sometimes you need something on your site in order for you to make money. So in certain situations we will give you  access to a wishlist item without you  paying and request that you pay monthly instead.
fields.extended: Life is tough sometimes we will always be there to support you.

fields.name: Security
fields.description: No one wants to be hacked or have their website taken advantage of select this option to find out more about how we avoid this!
fields.longdescription: At MakeWebWork we don’t reinvent the wheel, We use a secure framework on a secure platform. The platform is the Azure platform and the framework is Django. Azure is trusted by many government agencies. Django does not have any known exploits and as soon as one is discovered it is squashed very quickly. Django also runs on python which has an excellent track record for security.

fields.name: Price
fields.description: If price is your biggest concern you'll be pleased to know our goal is to keep costs low and we scale our costs based on your sites traffic. Select this to learn more about what we charge for and what they mean.
fields.longdescription: At MakeWebWork we treat all our customers like partners where we can celebrate your successes with you. There are three plans: build and bye, premium or partnership all with their own benefits. Build and bye is a process of building you a site and leaving you to support it yourself. Perfect if you already have a IT team ready to support it. Premium is a fixed rate payment monthly to host the website and any development is charged hourly or you can buy the prebuilt modules if they suit your needs and have them adapted to your site. Partnership is sharing your success. MakeWebWork will assess your business and either accept or decline you as a partner. If accepted, your website will be developed at a rapid pace adding new functionality and you get access to all modules at no cost once a partner, always a partner is the catch so when you’re making millions we will be getting a cut too. Getting there is the fun part! Read more on the price calculator link below.

fields.name: Design
fields.description: If one of your biggest concerns is how your website will look then please feel reassured you're the boss when it comes to designing your site! Select this option if you want to know how we design your site to make sure you love it!
fields.longdescription: Whether you’re good at designing things or not you are in safe hands. You can either tell us what you want or tell us to do it for you. It really is that simple. We will also have a designer available to you as a customer or to just browse. If you are interested in checking out the designer when it releases you can request a message to be notified when it drops! The goal is to have it be revolutionary.

fields.name: Uniqueness
fields.description: If the most important thing to you is to stand out from the crowd! Do something that's never been done before or make your customers say wow! Leave this highlighted.
fields.longdescription: At MakeWebWork our goal is to create partnerships with companies and create market leading brands. This is why you will always get more support here than any other company looking to build websites for you. We will always be there every step of the way.

fields.name: Flexibilty
fields.description: If you're thinking your online future has many potential paths and avenues to go down choose this option. We will let you know how we will welcome new ideas and avenues for your online presence.
fields.longdescription: At MakeWebWok we work with many different websites and are always implementing new things meaning that over time you will see many new functionalities emerge some maybe you wouldn't have thought of and some you'll lead and pave the way for. This is the beauty of what we do we aren't just creating websites we are creating a library of functions that can be shared among web owners. Of course noones implementation will look like yours so don't worry about that.

fields.name: Revenue
fields.description: If you are all about profit margins then choose this option and we will show you how we can make your finances work for you.
fields.longdescription: Our founder used to make 26 year financial plans and likely still does.. Besides this has drip fed through the company and he is always finding new ways to make graphs and at sometime in the future there will be accounting software built in! For now though we have focused on  having tables and creating clever AI to not only tell you your best sellers but also let you know what products are working and what maybe aren't. Soon we will even have a handy little AI assistant to recommend ideas to help your company grow promotions etc.

fields.name: People
fields.description: If you love working with humans click this. You're not old fashion don't worry we would love to chat to you and help you. Or just chat we do love a good chat!
fields.longdescription: At MakeWebWork we are always a phonecall away (within working hours of course). So maybe you're not sure how to do something or you've got an amazing idea that you have to get off your chest we will be there taking notes! Letting you know if that can happen and if so how long it will likely take!

fields.name: Easy development
fields.description: If you are a technical person resize this screen and watch as the page is resized the text will slip out of the box. The JavaScript file will catch this and resize all boxes to match to keep everything uniform.
fields.longdescription: At MakeWebWork we put the work in early so we don't have to in the future so if something is really boring for a developer there's a good chance we have automated it or made it easy. Scrolling animations are a good example of something we made very easy to implement don't even need to write code!

fields.name: New customers
fields.description: Are you looking to expand your audience?
fields.longdescription: Here at MakeWebWork, we can tailor your ad to suit any audience, whether that's your current demographic or a new one you want to explore!

fields.name: Brand visibility
fields.description: Want more people to recognize and trust your brand?
fields.longdescription: We help you stand out online with consistent, memorable branding that builds familiarity and credibility over time — from your website to social media and beyond.

fields.name: Lead generation
fields.description: Looking for more qualified leads?
fields.longdescription: Through targeted campaigns, and lead magnets, we bring in potential customers who are actually interested in what you offer.

fields.name: Sales growth
fields.description: Ready to boost your revenue?
fields.longdescription: Whether it's through better conversion rates, upsells, or abandoned cart recovery, we help you turn traffic into profit with eye catching visuals.

fields.name: Social media presence
fields.description: Want to stay active on the platform your audience is?
fields.longdescription: We can create engaging social media content that keeps your brand on their timelines — and drives real interactions.

fields.name: Content strategy
fields.description: Not sure what to say — or how to say it?
fields.longdescription: From blog posts to ad copy, we help you create valuable content that speaks your customer’s language and supports your goals.

fields.name: Full funnel marketing
fields.description: Want marketing that covers the whole customer journey?
fields.longdescription: From awareness to loyalty, we craft experiences that move people from curious visitors to loyal customers — and everything in between.

fields.name: Tailored strategy
fields.description: Tired of one-size-fits-all marketing?
fields.longdescription: At MakeWebWork, every strategy is built around your business, goals, and audience. No templates. No guessing. Just a plan that fits — and performs.

fields.name: Payments (stripe)
fields.description: This allows you to charge your customers using one off payments available methods are card, googlepay, applepay, paypal. This is done by integrating Stripe into the website. Stripe is a global payment processing platform they are a very reputable company and their fees are very reasonable they are able to process payments from around the globe from all different card providers and they even have a secure checkout process meaning we never have to store customers financial information.

fields.name: Direct debit (stripe)
fields.description: This will allow you to charge your customers monthly (for example subscriptions not suitable for spreading the cost of big purchases) This integration uses Stripe Stripe is a global payment processing platform they are a very reputable company and their fees are very reasonable they are able to process payments from around the globe from all different card providers and they even have a secure checkout process meaning we never have to store customers financial information.

fields.name: Calendar
fields.description: This is for companies that function using events or courses it is massively complemented by the events scheduler module and the advanced delivery module as it will allow  customers to see why delivery might take a little longer and when to expect events!

fields.name: Marketing Emails
fields.description: This module allows you to select a group of users based on many different criteria for example everyone with this product in their basket.  Anyone who has purchased in the last 5 months for example. Not only does it allow you to  email everyone in that group the same email but it also allows you to send emails that are personalised to every individual user with things like their names their birthdays or even their basket contents. It will also come with the ability to add flat discount rates to all that receive it.

fields.name: Advanced delivery date
fields.description: This module allows you to set your working hours and using those working hours it will automatically adjust any delivery dates to be realistic. For example if you have a product that takes 10 hours to make and you work 40 hours a week the system will adjust the delivery date to 3 days. If another customer orders their delivery date will be 3 days plus 3 days for the other customers item you can also set a flat delivery time to add on top such as 2 days postage the system if you have the calendar module will even go out of it's way to show the delivery dates and the creation time in different colours you can even set messages on the calendar page to let customers know that maybe something has come up and to expect a delay. Changing the hours you work will also change the  delivery dates for every customer waiting aswell to keep them in the loop. I will be using this module to  keep you updated on your websites and feature requests when you order. We recommend this to anyone creating bes

fields.name: Advanced marketing
fields.description: This module is extremely complex and is very difficult to adapt to individual sites so that's why the price is the highest. The reason is that  it takes a look at your customers footprint on your site making a note of groups. It will then send you a message to let you know that x amount of people have looked at this item in last 24 hours. Would you like to  email them and offer a discount to tempt them? The system will also sometimes ask users what they are upto or why they navigated away giving you an insight into why customers aren't buying. It's even clever enough to offer a discount to a customer if they have been looking at their basket for a little while. Another example that can be programmed into the system is recognising if a customer removes an item it will ask them if they wanted the item but couldn't afford it. It may then offer to discount the basket to cover the cost of the product if x% of the basket would've covered the cost of the item. Due to the fact that this is ext

fields.name: Web events scheduler
fields.description: This module allows you to schedule site wide events. These events can have effects like site wide discounts or  even something as complex as a site wide theme change.  It can also change logos add messages to the main page. Even something as simple as a name change like changing makewebwork to maywebwork for the month of may.

fields.name: E-Learning
fields.description: The E learning module will be  a combination of things it will mostly end up being a massive overhaul to the designer with  tasks and activities. We want it to be easy for a website owner to create an e- learning platform using the designer which is  a massive task as something as complex as an entire  E-learning module with right and wrong answers , quizzes,  activities, information, graphics and having them all line up and only allow them to be accessed by customers that have paid for the access is tough to make easy. We can see a path to that but it's going to be quite the journey there. If your company is aligned with this we may contact you to be part of testing and development no obligations though. Adding this module to your wishlist will help us determine demand aswell.

fields.name: Analytics
fields.description: This module is all about monitoring customer behaviour as they navigate through your website. Tracking things like their time on a page and where they visited allowing you to see what's popular and what's not. It also tracks basket items some of these will require cookies to function so be aware that customers may decline them.

fields.name: Active Directory
fields.description: This module is all about monitoring customer behaviour as they navigate through your website. Tracking things like their time on a page and where they visited allowing you to see what's popular and what's not. It also tracks basket items some of these will require cookies to function so be aware that customers may decline them.

fields.name: Database
fields.description: This module gives you access to the data you hold about your customers. We are working on graphical representations of this data to help you see things clearer but for now it will include all the data about every customer from order history to the last time they logged in.

fields.name: Finances
fields.description: This module is all about  finances and seeing what's profitable and what maybe isn't. This isn't applicable to all websites but to the ones that are it almost serves as your  very own product performance encyclopedia giving you the best and worst for profit and  even giving you an idea of what the most popular items are.

fields.name: Advanced analytics
fields.description: This module is all about understanding a customers choices on your site things like buttons hovered links hovered and collating this  information into a table for  the system to detect and point out improvents that could be made. For example is a customer hovers a link and doesn't click that means that something put them off if it happens  regularly or maybe they didn't realise they could click it.  Allowing you to request or  change things to benefit your customer base directly.
